  "canonical_definition": "A Coinage Probe is a methodology that introduces a coined term to a model in a fresh chat, measures its cold-state confabulation against a named set of near-neighbors, then introduces a single-sentence definition and re-measures distinguishability against the same neighbors — using the gap between the two measurements (Lexical Reachability) as evidence about the substrate on which the model's cognition runs.",
